\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Remote Access Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorization
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall authorize each remote access connection type prior to use,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-17 (Remote Access).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Managed Access Points
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall route all remote access traffic through authorized and managed network access control points,
 including VPN gateways.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged Remote Access
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall not execute privileged commands via remote access except where the IT Director (as LASO) has documented a compelling operational need,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-17(4) (Privileged Commands and Access).
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure information systems generate assessable evidence of all privileged remote access sessions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Cryptographic Protection of Remote Sessions
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall protect remote access sessions in transit consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Session Termination and Re-Authentication
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall configure remote access session termination and re-authentication consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


