\lang english
6.2 Wireless Networking Security
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Wireless Access Authorization
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall authorize each type of wireless access to County information systems prior to allowing such connections,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-18 (Wireless Access).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Validation and Inventory
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall perform validation testing for rogue wireless access points no less frequently than quarterly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall maintain a complete inventory of all County wireless access points.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall test access point range boundaries to determine the extent of wireless coverage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall design wireless coverage areas to remain within approved operational boundaries.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Physical and Logical Security
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall place wireless access points in secured areas to prevent unauthorized physical access and user manipulation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall logically separate the wireless network from the wired operational infrastructure using boundary protection mechanisms,
 including Virtual Local Area Networks (VLANs) and Access Control Lists (ACLs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall limit access between wireless and wired networks to operational needs only.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Required Authentication and Encryption
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall configure wireless access to County internal networks to use Wi-Fi Protected Access 2 (WPA2) or Wi-Fi Protected Access 3 (WPA3) Enterprise authentication and encryption,
 with cryptographic protections governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-18(1) (Authentication and Encryption).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Protocols
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall not deploy Wired Equivalent Privacy (WEP) or original Wi-Fi Protected Access (WPA) on County wireless infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Configuration Baselines
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall change default Service Set Identifiers (SSIDs) prior to deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall disable ad-hoc mode on County wireless infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall disable nonessential management protocols on County wireless infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall use management protocols whose cryptographic protections are consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Point Reset Procedures
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall invoke access point reset functions only to resolve a documented operational fault or to apply an approved configuration change.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall restore the access point to the latest approved configuration baseline defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.10"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 immediately following any reset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall not retain factory default configurations on County wireless infrastructure.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Point Logging
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall enable logging on all wireless access points.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall not deploy access points incapable of logging without an exception approved per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall forward wireless access point logs to the centralized log repository consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mobile Hotspots
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure County mobile devices authorized to access CJI such that any Wi-Fi hotspot function employs encryption,
 a non-default pre-shared key,
 port filtering,
 and connection restrictions to agency-controlled devices only.
 All County Personnel shall not transmit CJI over a mobile hotspot connection absent application-layer encryption that satisfies CJIS Security Policy requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Mobile Device Management (MDM)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enrollment Requirement
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall manage all County-owned mobile devices accessing CJI or County data through the centralized enterprise mobile device management (MDM) platform,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-19 (Access Control for Mobile Devices).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Controls
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure the MDM to enforce all of the following:
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote locking of County mobile devices on demand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote wiping of County mobile devices on demand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Detection of jailbroken or rooted devices,
 with automatic access blocking upon detection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Full-device or container-based encryption on managed devices,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-19(5) (Full Device or Container-Based Encryption).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Automatic device wipe after a maximum of ten (10) consecutive failed access attempts.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mobile Operating System Patching
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall apply mobile operating system patches consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mobile Device Encryption
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall encrypt CJI processed,
 stored,
 or transmitted on County mobile devices consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Bluetooth
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure the MDM to disable Bluetooth on CJI-authorized devices except where explicitly required for an approved operational purpose.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Where Bluetooth is approved,
 the Systems Administrator shall restrict associations to known agency-approved accessories only.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Where Bluetooth is approved,
 the Systems Administrator shall prevent users from creating unapproved Bluetooth associations on CJI-capable devices.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Transmission Methods
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall not transmit CJI using Short Message Service (SMS),
 Multimedia Messaging Service (MMS),
 or consumer voice or chat applications,
 including FaceTime and standard SMS.
 The Systems Administrator shall configure approved application-based communication tools used for CJI transmission to employ authentication and encryption mechanisms compliant with CJIS Security Policy requirements,
 independent of the device unlock authenticator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Cryptographic Key Extraction Protections
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure mobile devices to prevent extraction of stored certificates and cryptographic keys from the device hardware.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure certificates and cryptographic keys that grant special access or unique device identification for remote wipe on demand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure certificates and cryptographic keys that grant special access or unique device identification for self-deletion upon a defined number of unsuccessful access attempts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall manage cryptographic key generation,
 distribution,
 storage,
 destruction,
 and validation records for mobile devices consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Identification and Authentication
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
By Reference
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall configure identification and authentication for mobile and remote access consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 including multi-factor authentication baselines and mobile device advanced authentication with compensating-control exceptions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Personally Owned Devices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Prohibition
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall not use personally owned devices to access,
 process,
 store,
 or transmit Criminal Justice Information,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-20 (Use of External Systems).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Network Prohibition
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall deny personally owned devices connectivity to the County's internal trusted network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Limited External-Service Access
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All County Personnel may access County non-CJI cloud services from personally owned devices,
 including productivity suite web access,
 only where such access does not require enrollment of the personally owned device in the County mobile device management (MDM) platform.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All County Personnel shall not locally synchronize,
 download,
 cache,
 or persistently store Restricted or Confidential County data on personally owned devices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All County Personnel shall handle County data on personally owned devices consistent with the data classification and handling requirements in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to the prohibitions in this section shall be processed per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Vendor Remote Access
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compliance with This Policy
\series default
:
 Vendor remote access to County information systems shall comply with the requirements of this policy,
 including authorization,
 managed gateway routing,
 cryptographic protection,
 and session termination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Additional Vendor Obligations
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall require vendor compliance with the additional vendor-specific obligations defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 including least privilege,
 named-account-only provisioning,
 time-bounded authorization,
 persistent-tunnel prohibition,
 and vendor activity logging.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Mobile Device Incident Response
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Cybersecurity incident response activities triggered by mobile device events shall be conducted within the program established under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The following mobile-specific procedures supplement the Chapter 4 lifecycle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Initial Reporting
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall report the loss,
 theft,
 or suspected compromise of any County mobile device to the Assistant IT Director immediately upon discovery and no later than two (2) hours after discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Device Reporting Threshold
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall report the loss,
 theft,
 or suspected compromise of any CJI-authorized mobile device to the IT Director (as LASO) immediately and no later than one (1) hour after discovery,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section IR-6 (Incident Reporting).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Remote Lock and Wipe
\series default
:
 Upon notification of mobile device loss,
 theft,
 or suspected compromise,
 the Systems Administrator shall initiate remote lock and remote wipe procedures via the MDM platform within fifteen (15) minutes of notification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tiered Response Scenarios
\series default
:
 The Incident Commander designated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shall ensure response procedures address,
 at minimum,
 the following physical-control-loss scenarios:
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device known to be locked,
 loss of physical control for less than fifteen (15) minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device known to be locked,
 loss of physical control for fifteen (15) minutes or greater.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device lock state unknown,
 loss of physical control for less than fifteen (15) minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device lock state unknown,
 loss of physical control for fifteen (15) minutes or greater.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device known to be unlocked,
 any loss of physical control exceeding five (5) minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Total loss of device.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device compromise or suspected compromise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Device loss or compromise outside the United States.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 International Travel
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorization
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall not transport CJI-authorized devices outside the United States without prior written authorization from the IT Director (as LASO),
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Appendix G.4 (Mobile Device Guidance — Cellular Service Abroad).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Pre-Departure Inspection
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall perform a pre-departure inspection of each authorized device to verify Mobile Device Management enrollment,
 configuration baseline compliance,
 cryptographic protection,
 and managed-gateway connectivity,
 evidenced by a documented inspection record in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Post-Return Inspection
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall perform a post-return inspection of each authorized device within twenty-four (24) hours of its return to County custody,
 evidenced by a documented inspection record in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Foreign Network Exposure
\series default
:
 Any CJI-authorized device transported outside the United States shall be subject to a security assessment under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 prior to being returned to operational use,
 regardless of known foreign network connectivity.
\end_layout

